The paper focuses on evaluating API-misuse detectors, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the potential vulnerabilities and bugs that can arise from API misuses, which could fall under the cybersecurity (cs.CR) and systems (cs.SY) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the need for detectors to obtain additional usage examples to train their models, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
